pathway cycle.
(1) The collaborative shall conduct a comprehensive review of the
Statewide Priority Industry List established under Subsection A of this Section
not less frequently than once every two years. The first Biennial Priority Review
shall be completed not later than twenty-four months after the initial Priority
List is established pursuant to Paragraph (A)(2) of this Section. Subsequent
Biennial Priority Reviews shall be completed not later than twenty-four months
after the completion of the preceding review.
(2) The Biennial Priority Review is a distinct and independent process
from the five-year pathway reauthorization cycle established in R.S. 17:189.13.
Neither process satisfies nor substitutes for the other.
