shared performance framework review required under R.S. 17:189.3, include
in its assessment findings on stage-level implementation in the annual joint
performance report required under R.S. 17:189.3.
B. Stage I: Career awareness grades kindergarten through six.
(1) Stage I shall encompass grades kindergarten through six and shall be
designed to build foundational career awareness in students through age-
appropriate, structured activities that introduce students to the concept of
careers, connect academic learning to workplace applications, and provide
exposure to the range of career clusters and industry sectors reflected in the
Statewide Priority Industry List established pursuant to R.S. 17:189.4.
(2) Stage I activities shall be incorporated into the instructional program
